						               													<description>Like the Star Trek Starship Tactical Combat Simulator and its other book form expansions, the Ship Construction Manual is called a supplement for the Fasa Star Trek Role Playing Game but primarily has material for the Combat Simulator boardgame.  This supplement includes everything a player needs to generate all new starships, as well as all of the necessary statistics for the use in the Combat Simulator board game. In addition, there is background material usefull for the role playing game and some basic guidelines on creating deck plans based on your ship designs.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;From the cover:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Begin your career as a starship engineer.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Ship Construction Manual contains all the information necessary to construct starships for your STAR TREK Role Playing Game.  The recently declassified information in this manual allows the design of state-of-the-art starships of Federation, Klingon, Romulan, Gorn, or Orion origin. The easy-to-use format combined with the comprehensive data also provides the information necessary to build any ship active during the last 60 years of Star Trek history.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The 80-page rulebook includes the tables for the various engines, weapons, shields, and computers that make up starships, essays on the design philosophy of the major races, detailed information on the cost and availability of the equipment, and a system for rating the ships in combat.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Ship Construction Manual is required reading for all Star Fleet personnel and potential ship designers from all of the major races.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
